qx|a,hide|HT|b|cs|1|cp|4|fp||at|
^-{ Setting The Scene For 2 Way Checkback }
^-|cp|8|AT|
^b@2^*BMarty Bergen: ^*N|cp||at|When opener rebids 1NT, responder has the opportunity to use 2 Way Checkback. But of course he should not use it every time opener rebids 1NT. On the other hand, there are a lot of hands where we don't need to use 2 Way Checkback. But quite a few, as outlined below, do call for making use of this convention.
|cs|4|ht|h|at|^C{|ia|,1DP1HP1Np|at|}|at|^nand|HT|h|at|^o{|ia|,1CP1SP1Np|at|}|
HT|n|at|^C{|ia|,1DP1sP1Np|at|}|at|^nand|HT|n|at|^o{|ia|,1CP1hP1Np|at|} |
PG| ***** 14 ***** |


ht|r|at|^b@2
In addition to the above 4 auctions where opener bids a minor, responder bids a major, and opener rebids 1NT, you should also use 2 Way Checkback when the auctions start as illustrated below.|

HT|v|at|^C{|ia|,1cP1dP1Np|at|}|at|^nand|HT|v|at|^o{|ia|,1hP1sP1Np|at|}|
PG| ***** 15 ***** |


NT||
