qx|a,wide|cp|8|AT|
^b@2^*BMarty Bergen: ^*N|cp||at|The following conditions must be met before responder can use 2 Way Checkback.|ht|c|3d||fp|2|cs|4|at|

^-{ Opener rebids 1NT }
|at|

{ Responder has to be an unpassed hand }
|at|

{ 2 Way Checkback does apply regardless of whether 0, 1, or 2 major suits have been bid. }
|at|

{ The opponents are silent }
^-|ht|q|fp||cp||at|^b@2
Movie Maker: Marty, at the end of the lesson, addresses how a passed hand responder can deal with 2 Way Checkback.|
PG| ***** 16 ***** |


NT||
